Helen Lee Mei, a leading lady in Hong  Kong's film industry during the 1950s and 1960s, has died at age 63.
She died Thursday of cancer and pulmonary disease in Portland, Oregon.
Lee had top billing in all her 37 feature films and in 1960 became the  first foreign actress to star in a play at Tokyo's all-female Takarazuka  Theater.
She was born July 27, 1930 and left Hong Kong in 1967 to marry a US  Central Intelligence Agency officer she met in Taiwan. They divorced in 1982  but had been planning to remarry in June.
